.border(Color.gray)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, the first "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" element has the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"priority "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":" which causes its view to shrink dramatically due to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"higher priority of the second "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" element, even though all of their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other attributes (font, font size and character count) are the same."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A parent layout offers the child views with the highest layout priority"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all the space offered to the parent minus the minimum space required for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all its lower-priority children."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Ellipse/layoutPriority(_:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Ellipse\/layou